{"metadata":{"title":"Configuring Swift Package Manager","modules":[{"name":"App"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to configure your Swift Package Manager to use the package registry.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/app\/configuringspm"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Configuring Swift Package Manager using the command line","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Configuring-Swift-Package-Manager-using-the-command-line"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You will need to configure Swift Package Manager to be aware of the package registry server.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If you are running ","type":"text"},{"code":"swift-package-registy-server","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as localhost, then you can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tell Swift Package Manager this as follows:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["$ swift package-registry set --global --allow-insecure-http http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This will place this information in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/.swiftpm\/configuration\/registries.json"},{"type":"text","text":" and will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be global for all packages and projects on this machine."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On the other hand, if you only want to configure a single package or project, then leave"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"out the ","type":"text"},{"code":"--global","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag above:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["$ cd ~\/src\/some-project-to-configure","$ swift package-registry set --allow-insecure-http http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"then this will place this information in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~\/src\/some-project-to-configure\/.swiftpm\/configuration\/registries.json"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and thus will only apply to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"some-project-to-configure"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Changing-your-Packageswift-to-use-package-identifiers","type":"heading","text":"Changing your Package.swift to use package identifiers","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Normally, we are used to adding Github dependencies to a package manifest like this:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["let package = Package(","    name: \"MyPackage\",","    ...,","    dependencies: [","        .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-async-algorithms\", from: \"1.0.0\"),","        .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections.git\", from: \"1.1.4\"),","    ],","    targets: [","        .target(","            name: \"MyTarget\",","            dependencies: [","                .product(name: \"AsyncAlgorithms\", package: \"swift-async-algorithms\"),","                .product(name: \"Collections\", package: \"swift-collections\"),","            ]","        ),","    ],","    ...,",")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, if you want to use the package registry, then we would use package identifiers instead"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(in both the package-level and target-level dependencies):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let package = Package(","    name: \"MyPackage\",","    ...,","    dependencies: [","        .package(id: \"apple.swift-async-algorithms\", from: \"1.0.0\"),","        .package(id: \"apple.swift-collections\", from: \"1.1.4\"),","    ],","    targets: [","        .target(","            name: \"MyTarget\",","            dependencies: [","                .product(name: \"AsyncAlgorithms\", package: \"apple.swift-async-algorithms\"),","                .product(name: \"Collections\", package: \"apple.swift-collections\"),","            ]","        ),","    ],","    ...,",")"],"syntax":null},{"anchor":"Handling-transitive-dependencies","text":"Handling transitive dependencies","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the ","type":"text"},{"code":"MyPackage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" example above, have ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"direct"}]},{"type":"text","text":" dependency upon "},{"code":"swift-async-algorithms","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift-collections"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"However, if you look at the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Package.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift-async-algorithms"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["let package = Package(","  name: \"swift-async-algorithms\",","  ...,","  dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections.git\", from: \"1.0.4\"),","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-docc-plugin\", from: \"1.0.0\"),","  ],","  ...,"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"then we see that "},{"code":"swift-async-algorithms","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" depends on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift-collections"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"swift-docc-plugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"So ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MyPackage"},{"type":"text","text":" has a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"transitive","type":"text"}]},{"text":" dependency upon ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift-collections"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"swift-docc-plugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Therefore,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"MyPackage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has the following dependencies:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"direct"}]},{"type":"text","text":" dependency upon "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift-async-algorithms"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Both a ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"direct","type":"text"}]},{"text":" AND a ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"transitive","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" dependency upon "},{"code":"swift-collections","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"transitive","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" dependency upon "},{"code":"swift-docc-plugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift-collection"},{"text":" dependency:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Our ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"direct"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" dependency is via a package identifier","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Our "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"transitive"}]},{"text":" dependency is via a Github URL.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"So the question becomes: how should Swift Package Manager treat the two different ","type":"text"},{"code":"swift-collection","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" dependencies?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As explained "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/swiftlang\/swift-package-manager\/blob\/main\/Documentation\/PackageRegistry\/PackageRegistryUsage.md#using-registry-for-source-control-dependencies","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"we have three choices:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Option 1","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Treat “apple.swift-collections” and “https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections.git” as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"completely different dependencies. The “apple.swift-collections” dependency will be resolved via the package registry, and “https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections.git” will be resolved by cloning the respository.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that this option will likely result in duplicate symbol errors"}]},{"text":", since the identical library","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is included twice.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Option 2"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":". Still fetch “apple.swift-collections” from the registry and clone","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections.git”, but use the registry “lookup identifier” endpoint","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to determine if they are, in fact, the same dependency."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Option 3","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":". Use to registry’s “lookup identifier” endpoint to determine whether or not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections.git” is, in fact, the same as “apple.swift-collections”."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If it is, then replace all usages of “https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-collections.git” with “apple.swift-collections” and use the registry whenever possible."}]}]}]},{"level":2,"text":"Specifying transitive dependency policy via command line","type":"heading","anchor":"Specifying-transitive-dependency-policy-via-command-line"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If we are building using the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift"},{"type":"text","text":" command line, then we specify the above transitive dependency handling options like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Option 1: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--disable-scm-to-registry-transformation"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Option 2: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--use-registry-identity-for-scm"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Option 3: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--replace-scm-with-registry"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example:"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["$ cd ~\/src\/my-package","$ swift build --replace-scm-with-registry"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Specifying-transitive-dependency-policy-via-xcodebuild","text":"Specifying transitive dependency policy via xcodebuild","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are building using "},{"code":"xcodebuild","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", then you specify the transitive dependency policy via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"code":"-packageDependencySCMToRegistryTransformation","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" option:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Option 1: "},{"code":"-packageDependencySCMToRegistryTransformation none","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Option 2: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-packageDependencySCMToRegistryTransformation useRegistryIdentity"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Option 3: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-packageDependencySCMToRegistryTransformation useRegistryIdentityAndSources"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Side note: if building via "},{"code":"xcodebuild","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" you can also specify the default registry URL via","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-defaultPackageRegistryURL"},{"text":" option:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["xcodebuild -defaultPackageRegistryURL \"http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080\/\""]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Specifying-transitive-dependency-in-Xcode","text":"Specifying transitive dependency in Xcode","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can tell Xcode how to resolve transitive dependencies by setting an Xcode default:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["$ defaults write com.apple.dt.Xcode IDEPackageDependencySCMToRegistryTransformation <xcodebuild-option>"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"xcodebuild-option"},{"type":"text","text":" are the same as the options above for "},{"code":"xcodebuild","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Option 1: ","type":"text"},{"code":"none","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Option 2: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"useRegistryIdentity"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Option 3: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"useRegistryIdentityAndSources"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if you wanted the equivalent of the command-line "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--replace-scm-with-registry"},{"text":" option, you would do:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["$ defaults write com.apple.dt.Xcode IDEPackageDependencySCMToRegistryTransformation useRegistryIdentityAndSources"],"type":"codeListing"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App\/ConfiguringSPM"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App"]]},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App\/GithubAPI","doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App\/Architecture","doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App\/SpecificationSupport","doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App\/ToDoList"],"title":"Essentials","anchor":"Essentials","generated":true}],"references":{"doc://App/documentation/App/GithubAPI":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App\/GithubAPI","type":"topic","role":"article","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We can implement a Swift Package Registry Service by using these four operations in the Github API:"}],"title":"Github API","url":"\/documentation\/app\/githubapi"},"doc://App/documentation/App/GettingStarted":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App\/GettingStarted","type":"topic","role":"article","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to build and run the Swift Package Registry Service.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/app\/gettingstarted","title":"Getting started"},"doc://App/documentation/App/SpecificationSupport":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"Specification Support","abstract":[{"text":"See the status of each feature in the Swift Package Registry Service specification.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentat